Definition: the gradual transformation of habitable land into desert
Example: is usually caused by climate change or by destructive use of the land; the dust storms in Korea are the result of rapid desertification in China
Synonyms: geological_process, the, gradual, transformation, of, habitable, land, into, desert, is, usually, caused, by, climate, change, or, destructive, use, dust, storms, in, Korea, are, result, rapid, China
Category: noun.process
